paragraphs.text:
%md
Grant the following privileges to testuser in the MySQL database:

GRANT ALL ON airlinesdb.airline_raw to 'testuser’;
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

and confirm the grant is effective

mysql> SHOW GRANTS FOR 'testuser';
+----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Grants for testuser@%                                                |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| GRANT USAGE ON *.* TO 'testuser'@'%'                                 |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `airlinesdb`.`airline_raw` TO 'testuser'@'%' |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------+

Grant the following privileges to testuser in the MySQL database:

and confirm the grant is effective

+———————————————————————-+

paragraphs.title: 1. Create empty HDFS directory with appropriate permissions
paragraphs.text:
%sh
hdfs dfs -mkdir -p /user/zeppelin/airlines_raw
hdfs dfs -rm /user/zeppelin/airlines_raw/*
hdfs dfs -chown -R zeppelin:hive /user/zeppelin/airlines_raw
hdfs dfs -chmod -R 777 /user/zeppelin/airlines_raw

paragraphs.title: 2. Create an external table for the raw airline data
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS airlines_raw;
CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE airlines_raw (
 Year INT, 
 Month INT,
 DayofMonth INT,
 DayOfWeek INT,
 DepTime INT,
 CRSDepTime INT,
 ArrTime INT,
 CRSArrTime INT,
 UniqueCarrier STRING,
 FlightNum INT,
 TailNum STRING,
 ActualElapsedTime INT,
 CRSElapsedTime INT,
 AirTime INT,
 ArrDelay INT,
 DepDelay INT,
 Origin STRING,
 Dest STRING,
 Distance INT,
 TaxiIn INT,
 TaxiOut INT,
 Cancelled INT,
 CancellationCode STRING,
 Diverted STRING,
 CarrierDelay INT,
 WeatherDelay INT,
 NASDelay INT,
 SecurityDelay INT,
 LateAircraftDelay INT
)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
LOCATION '/user/zeppelin/airlines_raw';
DESCRIBE airlines_raw;

%sh
rm /home/zeppelin/./airline_raw.java
hdfs dfs -rm -R /user/zeppelin/airlines_raw
#sqoop import --connect jdbc:mysql://ip-172-31-0-110.eu-central-1.compute.internal:3306/airlinesdb --username testuser --password BadPass#1 --table airline_raw --split-by Year --hive-import --hive-table default.airlines_raw
sqoop import --connect jdbc:mysql://ip-172-31-6-78.eu-central-1.compute.internal:3306/airlinesdb --username testuser --table airline_raw --split-by Year --target-dir /user/zeppelin/airlines_raw --input-fields-terminated-by ','

paragraphs.title: 7. Determine the amount of canceled flights by month and year for each airline
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)
SELECT uniquecarrier, count(cancelled) AS canceledflightsamount, year, month FROM airlines GROUP BY uniquecarrier, year, month ORDER BY uniquecarrier,year ASC,month ASC

paragraphs.title: 8. How many flights were considered late by month and year for each  airline?
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)
SELECT uniquecarrier, count(*) AS lateflights, year, month FROM airlines WHERE arrdelay > 0 GROUP BY uniquecarrier, year, month ORDER BY uniquecarrier,year ASC,month ASC

paragraphs.title: 9. Determine the unique carrier with the highest delays (NASDelay and SecurityDelay)
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)
SELECT uniquecarrier, count(NASDelay) + count(SecurityDelay) AS totaldelay FROM airlines GROUP BY uniquecarrier ORDER BY totaldelay DESC LIMIT 1

paragraphs.title: 10. Determine the unique carrier with the least delays
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive)
SELECT uniquecarrier, count(NASDelay) + count(SecurityDelay) AS totaldelay FROM airlines GROUP BY uniquecarrier ORDER BY totaldelay ASC LIMIT 1
